{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Tutorial 01: Getting Started
",
    "
",
    "This tutorial demonstrates the simplest way to run a training experiment using the high-level `run_unified_training` interface in the `fishy-business` library."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Imports
",
    "
",
    "First, we'll import the necessary components: `TrainingConfig` for defining our experiment and `run_unified_training` for executing it."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from fishy import TrainingConfig, run_unified_training, display_final_summary
",
    "import os"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Define a Minimal Configuration
",
    "
",
    "The `TrainingConfig` object centralizes all hyperparameters and experimental settings. Here, we specify the model architecture, the dataset name, and the path to the data file."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Define a minimal configuration
",
    "config = TrainingConfig(
",
    "    model="transformer",
",
    "    dataset="species",
",
    "    file_path="../../data/REIMS.xlsx", # Adjust path if necessary
",
    "    epochs=5,
",
    "    batch_size=32,
",
    "    wandb_log=False,
",
    ")
",
    "
",
    "print(f"Launching a {config.model} training on the {config.dataset} dataset...")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Run the Experiment
",
    "
",
    "The `run_unified_training` function handles the orchestration of data loading, model initialization, and the training loop."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Run the experiment
",
    "results = run_unified_training(config)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Inspect Results
",
    "
",
    "Finally, we can use `display_final_summary` to view a formatted summary of the experiment's performance."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Inspect the results using the summary table
",
    "display_final_summary(results)"
   ]
  }
 ],
